</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2B4BC6FF8C4023FF302233FCBBD9C8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488278" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6488278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488278/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" startId="10.[151,250,1900,1924]" targetBox="[221,1364,181,1873]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BEB1B4EFF8C4023FF302233FCBBD9C8" blockId="10.[151,1437,1900,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FF302233FEB0D9BC" bold="true" box="[151,273,1900,1924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8C4023FEB12232FD99D9BC" authority="Saigusa, 2022" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="2022" box="[278,568,1900,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oshimai" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Sphenempis">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FEB12232FEF4D9BC" box="[278,341,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Empis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FEC52233FE7AD9BC" box="[354,475,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Sphenempis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FE4F2233FD99D9BC" box="[488,568,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">oshimai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FD9A2233FD2DD9BC" bold="true" box="[573,652,1900,1924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2137A27FF8C4023FD9A2233FD2DD9BC" box="[573,652,1900,1924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male. A, B, E. holotype; C, D, F, G–I, paratype. 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FBCA2233FB27D9BC" bold="true" box="[1133,1158,1900,1924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">A,</emphasis>
hind femur, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FF3022CFFF0FD990" bold="true" box="[151,174,1936,1960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">B,</emphasis>
hind tibia, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FE6122CFFE7ED990" bold="true" box="[454,479,1936,1960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">C,</emphasis>
mid femur, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FCA722CFFCB9D990" bold="true" box="[768,792,1936,1960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">D,</emphasis>
mid tibia, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FB8C22CFFBE3D990" bold="true" box="[1067,1090,1936,1960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">E,</emphasis>
distal part of hind femur, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FF4122EBFF58D9F4" bold="true" box="[230,249,1972,1996]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">F,</emphasis>
distal part of mid femur, anterior aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FD0A22EBFD66D9F4" bold="true" box="[685,711,1972,1996]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">G,</emphasis>
terminalia, lateral aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FC7C22EBFC54D9F4" bold="true" box="[987,1013,1972,1996]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">H,</emphasis>
ditto, dorsal aspect; 
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8C4023FB6822EBFB41D9F4" bold="true" box="[1231,1248,1972,1996]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">I,</emphasis>
ditto, dorsolateral aspect. Scale bars = 0.5 mm (A–F), 0.2 mm (G), 0.1 mm (H, I).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEB1B4EFF8D4022FF6024CCFB79DCBD" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
Most structural and chaetotaxy characters as in description of subgenus stated above. Legs (
<figureCitation id="136F07CBFF8D4022FB7C24CCFAF8DF96" box="[1243,1369,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[219,1369,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Empis (Sphenempis) oshimai sp. nov., male.A, B, E. holotype; C, D, F, G–I, paratype.A, hind femur, anterior aspect; B, hind tibia, anterior aspect; C, mid femur, anterior aspect; D, mid tibia, anterior aspect; E, distal part of hind femur, anterior aspect; F, distal part of mid femur, anterior aspect; G, terminalia, lateral aspect; H, ditto, dorsal aspect; I, ditto, dorsolateral aspect. Scale bars = 0.5 mm (A–F), 0.2 mm (G), 0.1 mm (H, I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488278/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figs 6A–F</figureCitation>
): Mid femur with 2–4 anteroventral and 1–2 posteroventral spines, hind femur slightly longer than 12 times its thickness, with 4–6 anteroventral spines, no posteroventral spines, with weaker anterior preapical seta. Wing (
<figureCitation id="136F07CBFF8D4022FAA82484FAC6DFCD" box="[1295,1383,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,309,1083]" captionTargetId="figure-73@6.[156,1431,309,1091]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wings of Empis species. A, Empis (Sphenempis) bicoloriventris sp. nov., paratype male from Okinawa-jima; B, Empis (Sphenempis) amurensis, male; C, Empis (Sphenempis) oshimai sp. nov., paratype male; D, Empis (Lissempis) nigritarsis, female; E, Empis sp. close to E. kasparyani, male from Kagoshima, Kyushu; F, Empis leptogastra Loew, male. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488272/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) 3.2 times as long as wide; cell r 
<subScript id="17D0190BFF8D4022FE6D274EFE45DC27" attach="left" box="[458,484,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">2+3</subScript>
1.5 times as wide as cell r 
<subScript id="17D0190BFF8D4022FCA0274EFC80DC27" attach="left" box="[775,801,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">4+5</subScript>
at level of tip of vein R 
<subScript id="17D0190BFF8D4022FB80274EFBE1DC27" attach="left" box="[1063,1088,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">2+3</subScript>
; discal cell short, 0.44 times as long as vein M 
<subScript id="17D0190BFF8D4022FE9C276AFEE2DC7B" attach="left" box="[315,323,565,579]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">1</subScript>
; axillary lobe wider than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8D4022FDDE277CFCBFDC05" authority="Saigusa, 2022" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="2022" box="[633,798,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloriventris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8D4022FDDE277CFCBFDC05" box="[633,798,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">bicoloriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8D4022FC83277CFCDDDC05" bold="true" box="[804,892,547,573]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2137A27FF8D4022FC83277CFCDDDC05" box="[804,892,547,573]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, widest at basal 1/3, with margin strongly curved before middle. Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="136F07CBFF8D4022FE6E2718FDE0DC5A" box="[457,577,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[219,1369,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Empis (Sphenempis) oshimai sp. nov., male.A, B, E. holotype; C, D, F, G–I, paratype.A, hind femur, anterior aspect; B, hind tibia, anterior aspect; C, mid femur, anterior aspect; D, mid tibia, anterior aspect; E, distal part of hind femur, anterior aspect; F, distal part of mid femur, anterior aspect; G, terminalia, lateral aspect; H, ditto, dorsal aspect; I, ditto, dorsolateral aspect. Scale bars = 0.5 mm (A–F), 0.2 mm (G), 0.1 mm (H, I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488278/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figs 6G–I</figureCitation>
): Palm-like process with two short, finger-like distal lobes; dentate proximal lobe minute; three lobes shorter than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8D4022FDF22734FD5BDCBD" authority="Saigusa, 2022" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="2022" box="[597,762,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloriventris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8D4022FDF22734FD5BDCBD" box="[597,762,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">bicoloriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8D4022FCA62734FCFBDCBD" bold="true" box="[769,858,619,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2137A27FF8D4022FCA62734FCFBDCBD" box="[769,858,619,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; cercus weakly raised posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB1B4EFF8D4022FF6027D0FE03DC91" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,418,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8D4022FF6027D0FE84DC91" bold="true" box="[199,293,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
